HEADWORD: Fulfillment
<hw>Ful*fill"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>fulfilment</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of fulfilling; accomplishment; completion;
<as>as, the <ex>fulfillment</ex> of prophecy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Execution; performance; <as>as, the
<ex>fulfillment</ex> of a promise</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fulgency</ent>⟦br⟧
